The net present value can be solved by using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Net present value}&=\dfrac{\text{Cashflow Year 1}}{(1+\text{Required return})^1}+\dfrac{\text{Cashflow Year 2}}{(1+\text{Required return})^2}\\
&+\dfrac{\text{Cashflow Year 3}}{(1+\text{Required return})^3}+\dfrac{\text{Cashflow Year 4}}{(1+\text{Required return})^4}\\
&+\dfrac{\text{Cashflow Year 5}}{(1+\text{Required return})^5}-\text{Total cash outflow}
\end{aligned}$$
